<emphasis id="B926D14F0974B22AE873FC2B24B74E38" box="[1137,1212,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="483">gobius</emphasis>
= gudgeon; 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0974B22AE942FC2B20F44E1C" baseAuthorityName="Fowler" baseAuthorityYear="1934" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Favonigobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="32" pageNumber="483" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="melanobranchus">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0974B22AE942FC2B20F44E1C" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="483">melanobranchus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: refers to the pigmented area in the median part of branchiostegal membranes in adult males.
</paragraph>
